    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen a Dockerfile has an `escape` parser directive...\r\n\r\n```\r\n# escape=`\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nat its top, it's escape character is now \\` instead of  `\\`.\r\n\r\nSyntax is highlighted improperly when this option is set.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSyntax should highlighted as if the escape character is that which is set.\r\n\r\nSee [Dockerfile reference](https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/builder/#parser-directives)",
